com.matrixone.apps.domain
Interface DomainSymbolicConstants

All Known Implementing Classes:
CurrencyConversion, DomainObject, FormatUtil, Image, Job, UnitConversion
public interface DomainSymbolicConstants

The DomainSymbolicConstants interface defines all the symbolic names as static final Strings. To get actual names at runtime use the PropertyUtil.getSchemaProperty method that takes a Context as the first parameter. If in a bean or JPO that extends DomainObject, you should just pass the symbolic constant as the second arguement. For example: String isVersionObjectAttr = PropertyUtil.getSchemaProperty(context, SYMBOLIC_attribute_IsVersionObject); If you are in a JSP, you should pass the symbolic constant with "DomainObject." prepended. For example: String isVersionObjectAttr = PropertyUtil.getSchemaProperty(context, DomainObject.SYMBOLIC_attribute_IsVersionObject);

Version:
AEF 10.5 - Copyright (c) 2001, MatrixOne, Inc.
